    <name>Ennerdale Horseshoe</name>
    <bounds minlat="54.4803917" minlon="-3.3757119" maxlat="54.5280189" maxlon="-3.2133571" />
  </metadata>
  <rte>
    <name>Ennerdale Horseshoe</name>
	<desc>There are several recognised Lake District horseshoe walks, but surely none of them can be more of an endurance test than this one. The summits, if all included, read a bit like a Lakeland hall of fame: Red Pike, High Stile, High Crag, Haystacks, Green Gable, Great Gable, Kirk Fell and Pillar.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1082-description</url>
	<urlname>Walk - Ennerdale Horseshoe</urlname>
      
